55. The Captivi is recommended as a moral play; the Asinaria as a witty one (Asin. prol. 13 Inest lepos beatusque iu kae comoedia, Ridicula res est); the Heautontimorumenos for its diction (Haut. prol. 46 Iu hac est pura oratio). This practice of ‘puffing one’s wares' in the prologue seems to have been widely spread among Comedians. A grammarian quotes in illustration of the Old Latin adverb prime a line from the prologue of Naevius' ‘Acontizomenos⁷: Acontizomenos subula est prime proba. The epilogue to the Captivi repeats the recommendation, vv. 1029 sqq. :
